Firefox Sync Client version 0.04
================================

This module provides an API to connect to a Firefox Sync Server.

For now it is only possible to get a collection of things from the server.
Later it will also be possible to change items on the server.

Requests to the server can be cached in a temporary file.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


DEPENDENCIES

You will need the following modules and their dependencies from CPAN:

    Digest::SHA
    Crypt::Rijndael
    JSON
    LWP::UserAgent
    LWP::Protocol::https
    MIME::Base32
    MIME::Base64
    Storable


EXAMPLES

After installation, you can find examples in the pod documentation of the
module. Call it with:

    perldoc Firefox::Sync::Client


